  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Regional anesthesia may decrease the release of endogenous opioids, increase Natural Killer
      cell (NK) function and decrease development of metastasis. The recent analysis of the Cancer
      Registry has noted an improved 5-year survival in patients who received epidural analgesia
      during surgery for colorectal carcinoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
